# SS1 Perception — Cube Detection & Pose Estimation

**Team:** Stackbot | **Unit:** UTS 41069 Robotics Studio 2
**Author:** Arjun Harish (25533997) — Subsystem 1 (Perception)

> Detects 6 coloured cubes (3 red, 2 yellow, 1 blue) using an Intel RealSense D435i camera and publishes their 3D positions in `base_link` frame for the robot arm to pick up.

---

## What This Subsystem Does

The camera on the robot wrist looks at the table. This node:
1. Finds each cube by colour (HSV masking)
2. Rejects noise and duplicate detections (NMS + squareness filter)
3. Measures how far away each cube is (depth from RealSense)
4. Converts pixel positions → real-world XYZ coordinates (in metres, relative to `base_link`)
5. Smooths the positions over time so the robot gets stable readings
6. Publishes the results so SS3 (Saikat) can send pick commands to SS2 (Khoa)

---

## Files in This Package

```
ros2_ws_backup/src/perception_pkg/perception_pkg/
├── pose_estimator_v2.py           ← Main node — USE THIS ONE
├── pose_estimator.py              ← Original backup — DO NOT modify
├── charuco_handeye_calibration.py ← Run once to calibrate camera↔robot
├── charuco_handeye_validate.py    ← Check calibration accuracy
└── publish_handeye_tf.py          ← Publishes the camera transform

ros2_ws_backup/src/perception_pkg/calibration/
├── handeye_charuco_park.json      ← BEST result (1.84mm std) ← USE THIS
├── handeye_charuco_tsai.json
├── handeye_charuco_daniilidis.json
├── handeye_charuco_horaud.json
└── handeye_charuco_andreff.json
```

---

## Prerequisites

### Hardware
- UR3e robot at **192.168.0.192** (always ping first — IP can change)
- Intel RealSense D435i (wrist-mounted)
- OnRobot RG2-FT gripper

### Software
- Ubuntu 22.04 + ROS2 Humble + Python 3.10 + OpenCV 4.5.4
- `ros2_ws` must be built first (robot driver + MoveIt)

### Install dependencies (one-time)
```bash
sudo apt install ros-humble-tf-transformations
sudo apt install libnet1-dev
```

---

## Quick Start

> Run each command in a **separate terminal**, in this order.

### Terminal 1 — Camera
```bash
source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
ros2 launch realsense2_camera rs_launch.py \
  rgb_camera.color_profile:=1280x720x30 \
  depth_module.profile:=640x480x30 \
  enable_depth:=true \
  align_depth.enable:=true \
  publish_tf:=false
```

### Terminal 2 — Robot Driver
```bash
source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
source ~/ros2_ws/install/setup.bash
ros2 launch ur_robot_driver ur_control.launch.py \
  ur_type:=ur3e \
  robot_ip:=192.168.0.192 \
  kinematics_params_file:=/home/arjun/my_robot_calibration_192.yaml \
  launch_rviz:=false
```
> ⚠️ Use the full path `/home/arjun/` — never `~/` for `kinematics_params_file`

### Terminal 3 — Hand-Eye Transform
```bash
cd ~/ros2_ws_backup && source install/setup.bash
ros2 run perception_pkg publish_handeye_tf --method park
```

### Terminal 4 — Pose Estimator (Main Node)
```bash
cd ~/ros2_ws_backup && source install/setup.bash
ros2 run perception_pkg pose_estimator_v2
```

A window will open showing the camera feed with coloured bounding boxes on each cube.

---

## Verify It's Working

```bash
# Should print: red,red,red,yellow,yellow,blue
ros2 topic echo /object_labels

# Should print 6 poses in base_link frame
ros2 topic echo /raw_detected_objects

# Check TF chain is connected
ros2 run tf2_ros tf2_echo base_link camera_color_optical_frame
```

---

## Topics Published

| Topic | Type | Contents |
|---|---|---|
| `/raw_detected_objects` | `geometry_msgs/PoseArray` | 3D poses of all detected cubes in `base_link` frame |
| `/object_labels` | `std_msgs/String` | Colour labels e.g. `red,red,red,yellow,yellow,blue` |

> ⚠️ **SS3 note (Saikat):** Subscribe to `/raw_detected_objects` — it was renamed from `/ss1/raw_detected_objects` in Session 7.

