## Testing Without a Robot

You can test detection without the real robot using a fake transform:

```bash
# Instead of Terminal 2 (robot driver), run this:
source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
ros2 run tf2_ros static_transform_publisher \
  --x 0 --y 0 --z 0.5 \
  --qx 0 --qy 0 --qz 0 --qw 1 \
  --frame-id base_link \
  --child-frame-id tool0
```

Then run Terminals 1, 3, and 4 as normal. Positions won't be physically accurate but detection and labels will work.

