## New Session Checklist

Run these every time before starting:

```bash
# 1. Confirm robot IP hasn't changed
ping 192.168.0.192

# 2. Check camera serial number
rs-enumerate-devices | grep Serial

# 3. If serial changed → update intrinsics
ros2 topic echo /camera/camera/color/camera_info --once
# Copy FX, FY, CX, CY into pose_estimator_v2.py and rebuild

# 4. If camera serial changed → redo hand-eye calibration (see below)
```

### Current Camera Intrinsics (Session 7)
```
Serial : 017322075373
FX     : 917.7413940429688
FY     : 917.1574096679688
CX     : 645.986572265625
CY     : 349.41644287109375
```
These are set at the top of `pose_estimator_v2.py`. Update them if the camera changes.

